    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned i need to set up an escrow account for the house i'm buying in toronto. i've never heard of that before... what exactly is escrow and why do i need it for the closing?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow, in the context of buying a house in Toronto, is essentially a temporary holding account, which is a bit like a very secure, neutral-ground holding pen for your money and the property documents. Think of it like a highly regulated, temporary safe where your earnest money and the final purchase funds are kept until *all* the conditions of the sale are met. You need it because it protects both you, the buyer, and the seller, ensuring that the money isn't released until the title is properly transferred and all the paperwork is signed off. It's a crucial step to make sure the entire transaction goes smoothly and doesn't fall apart at the last minute.",
      "source": "target",
