    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "so if it's a lawyer or a brokerage holding it, what happens if there's a mistake or if a dispute comes up? like if the seller says they didn't get the full amount, how does the escrow process handle that conflict?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If a dispute arises, like if the seller claims they haven't received the full amount, the escrow agent—the lawyer or brokerage—steps in as the impartial referee. They don't just blindly hand over the cash; they hold the funds until all contractual obligations are satisfied. If there's a disagreement, the escrow agent freezes the funds and facilitates communication between both parties, often requiring legal intervention to resolve the discrepancy before any money moves. This entire system is designed to prevent one party from being cheated by the other.",
